What are the accepted input file formats?

Genoppi currently accepts i) experimental quantitative interaction proteomics data from immunoprecipitations (IP) followed by tandem mass spectrometry (MS/MS) results of bait pull down or ii) the MS/MS results from a full proteome analysis. The input file must be a text file that includes

  • HGNC approved symbol, or
  • UniProt accession numbers, followed by
  • results of the one-sample moderated t-test on two replicates: p and FDR values, or
  • logFC values for two replicates observed in the IP experiment.

All fields must be filled with no missing values.

Here are examples of correct column headers and accepted values.

1. HGNC symbol and logFC for two replicates



2. UniProt accession numbers and logFC for two replicates



3. HGNC symbol and results of statistical analyses



4. UniProt accession numbers and results of statistical analyses

What if my file is an Excel spreadhseet?

If your data is in Excel format and you are a Mac user, please convert to text file by selecting ‘File’ -> ‘Save As…’ and choose ‘Windows Formatted Text’ option as shown below.
